Skincare Product Description Guidelines for Shopify

Primary Goals:
	1.	Educate and convert real customers with clear, benefit-focused content.
	2.	Rank in search engines by matching real user intent with optimized, high-quality SEO content.

Critical Requirements
• Accuracy first: All information must be 100% verifiable from the official manufacturer source. No assumptions or added claims unless explicitly supported.
• Skincare only: These guidelines apply only to skincare products (serums, moisturizers, toners, eye creams, sunscreens, exfoliants, masks, essences, acne treatments, etc.). Do not apply to makeup, hair care, body care, tools, oral care, or fragrance.
• Language versions:
• English version is required by default.
• Arabic version is created only if (a) explicitly requested and (b) provided with the exact Arabic product name.
• Tags separation: Always use English commas (,) to separate tags—even if the tag text is Arabic or transliterated. Shopify interprets only English commas as delimiters; other separators break tagging.

⸻
	1.	Process Overview
	1.	Confirm category: Ensure the product is a skincare product.
	2.	Keyword research: Build the English keyword list before writing. Include brand variations, high-intent search phrases, product type, skin concerns, and benefits.
	3.	Write description: Follow the structure below exactly, starting with the SEO-focused opening paragraph.
	4.	Supplementary SEO elements: Create Title, Meta Description, Tags, Alt Text, and Tips/Warnings based on the same official source.
	5.	Review/verify: Run through the final checklist.
	6.	Arabic version (if applicable): Only after both conditions are met, adapt the content into Arabic following the parallel structure.

⸻
	2.	Writing and Formatting Rules
• Tone and purpose: Clear, helpful, benefit-oriented, with precise terminology. Avoid fluff, vague hype, or unsupported superlatives (e.g., skip “amazing” unless brand uses it and source supports it).
• Headings: Use <strong> only for section titles.
• Paragraphs: Default size; no inline style or manual font-size changes.
• HTML structure:
• Use <strong> for headings.
• Use <ul class="-mt-1 list-disc space-y-2 pl-8"> with <li class="whitespace-normal break-words"> for lists (Key Benefits, Skin Types, Skin Concerns).
• Use <ol class="-mt-1 list-decimal space-y-2 pl-8"> for step-by-step usage.
• Always insert <br><br> between major sections for readability.
• How to Use → Ingredients spacing: If “How to Use” is a list or paragraph, there must be <br><br> immediately after it before <strong>Ingredients:</strong> so they do not run together.
• No inline styles, no color definitions, no data-mce-style attributes.
• Keyword inclusion: Do not start the description until the English keyword list is complete and reflects real customer search behavior.

⸻
	3.	SEO Keyword Rules
• Build a focused English keyword list before writing. Include:
• Brand name + common misspellings/variants (spacing, transliteration, case).
• Product type (e.g., “hydrating face serum,” “non-comedogenic moisturizer”).
• Skin concerns targeted (e.g., “dark spots,” “fine lines,” “dry skin treatment”).
• Benefits/results (e.g., “brightening,” “pore-minimizing,” “dewy glow”).
• Intent combinations: brand + concern, product + format + benefit (e.g., “Korean vitamin C serum for hyperpigmentation”).
• Avoid overly broad terms like “skincare” alone; prioritize mid- and high-intent phrases.
• The first sentence must naturally contain: brand name, product type, and at least one high-intent keyword phrase.

⸻
	4.	Description Structure (English)

[Product Name]
[Before writing: complete and optimize the English keyword list for skincare.]

• Do not begin writing until the English keyword list is complete and intentionally reflects customer search behavior.
• Include brand name and its common spelling/variant forms in keywords.
• Focus keyword combinations on brand + product type + skin concern or benefit.
• First sentence must include brand name, product type, and one or more high-intent skincare keywords naturally.
• Opening paragraph: 80–180 words explaining who it’s for, what it does, how it works (core mechanism), and what differentiates it. Human-first, SEO-aligned.
• Start writing the English description directly inside the code block without extra heading labels.
• Use <br><br> after the opening paragraph.

[Start code block here]
[Opening paragraph 80–180 words with brand name, product type, high-intent keyword(s), clear benefit proposition and differentiation.]

<br><br>

<strong>Key Benefits</strong>

<ul class="-mt-1 list-disc space-y-2 pl-8">
    <li class="whitespace-normal break-words">Benefit 1 (e.g., reduces redness and irritation)</li>
    <li class="whitespace-normal break-words">Benefit 2 (e.g., boosts hydration for plumper skin)</li>
    <li class="whitespace-normal break-words">Benefit 3 (e.g., improves texture and minimizes pores)</li>
    <!-- Add 3–7 outcome-focused benefits -->
</ul>

<br>

<strong>Skin Types</strong>

<ul class="-mt-1 list-disc space-y-2 pl-8">
    <li class="whitespace-normal break-words">[Only applicable types: All skin types / Dry / Oily / Combination / Sensitive / Normal]</li>
</ul>

<br>

<strong>Skin Concerns</strong>

<ul class="-mt-1 list-disc space-y-2 pl-8">
    <li class="whitespace-normal break-words">[Relevant concerns, e.g., dehydration, hyperpigmentation, aging, dullness, acne, uneven tone]</li>
</ul>

<br>

<strong>How to Use</strong>

<!-- Step-by-step if applicable: -->
<ol class="-mt-1 list-decimal space-y-2 pl-8">
    <li class="whitespace-normal break-words">Step 1 (e.g., apply after cleansing and toning)</li>
    <li class="whitespace-normal break-words">Step 2 (e.g., follow with moisturizer)</li>
</ol>

<br><br> <!-- ALWAYS include this gap before Ingredients when using a list -->

<!-- Or paragraph if steps are not discrete -->
[Write as a single paragraph noting time of use (morning/evening), layering order, frequency, and any preparation/post notes.]

<br><br> <!-- ALWAYS include this gap before Ingredients when using a paragraph -->

<strong>Ingredients:</strong> [Full official INCI list in Title Case, comma-separated, in the order provided by the manufacturer if given.]

<br><br>

[Optional additional short closing if brand style includes usage context or pairing suggestions.]

[End code block here]

⸻
	5.	Supplementary SEO & Conversion Fields (each in its own copyable code block, no labels inside the block)

Tips and Warnings

• Provide 2–4 actionable, context-aware tips or cautions based strictly on official info. Examples:
Use in the evening when layering with retinol.
Always apply sunscreen during the day when using AHAs.
Patch test if skin is sensitive.
Start slowly with potent actives and increase frequency over time.

Tags

• Comma-separated. Include brand name variations, product type, concern, benefit, common misspellings, transliterations.
• Always use English commas.
Examples:
English: the ordinary, niacinamide serum, brightening serum, oily skin treatment, face hydration
Arabic/translit: ذا اورديناري, نياسيناميد سيروم, سيروم تفتيح, علاج البشرة الدهنية, ترطيب الوجه

Page Title

[Brand Name] [Product Name] | [Primary Benefit or Feature]
• 60–70 characters max (ideal 55–65).
• Starts with brand name.

Meta Description

• 140–155 characters.
• Include brand, product type, key benefit or ingredient.
Example:
BrandName Vitamin C Serum brightens dark spots and evens skin tone. Lightweight formula delivers antioxidant protection and radiant glow.

Media Alt Text

• 5 variations, each under 125 characters, including brand + product + key feature.
Examples:
BrandName Vitamin C Serum for Brightening
Hydrating Face Serum by BrandName with Hyaluronic Acid
BrandName Anti-Aging Serum for Fine Lines
Lightweight Glow Serum BrandName for Uneven Skin Tone
BrandName Skin Plumping Serum with Peptides

⸻
	6.	Categorization (for Shopify fields)

Shopify Category:
Health & Beauty > Personal Care > Cosmetics > Skin Care > [most specific, e.g., Face Serums, Moisturizers, Eye Creams, Sunscreen]

Product Type:
Short, general label (e.g., Serum, Moisturizer, Toner, Eye Cream, Sunscreen, Exfoliant)

Collections:
• Select only from the approved internal collection hierarchy.
• If the needed collection does not exist in the provided “My Collection List,” do not guess or substitute—flag for review or request addition.
• A product may belong to multiple collections only if it genuinely fits each.
• Exact match required (hierarchy and spelling).
• Do not use deprecated or unofficial labels.

Example correct: SKIN CARE > Serum & Treatments > Face Serum
Example incorrect (should be flagged): SKIN CARE > Serums if “Serums” isn’t defined.

